President Biden has declared a major disaster in Tennessee due to severe winter storms that occurred from February 11 to February 19, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in several counties. Hazard mitigation measures will also be funded statewide. Myra M. Shird has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.